Package io.artframework

Interface Factory<TContext extends ArtObjectContext<TArtObject>,​TArtObject extends ArtObject>

  • Type Parameters:
    TContext - the type of the context that is created for the art object by the factory
    TArtObject - the art object type that is created by the factory, e.g. Action
    All Superinterfaces:
    Scoped
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ActionFactory<TTarget>, RequirementFactory<TTarget>, TriggerFactory
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFactory, DefaultActionFactory, DefaultRequirementFactory, DefaultTriggerFactory
    public interface Factory<TContext extends ArtObjectContext<TArtObject>,​TArtObject extends ArtObject>
extends Scoped
    The Factory is used to create new instances of ArtObjects which are wrapped inside an ArtObjectContext. The created context and art object is initialized with its configuration and properties.

    Every ArtObject must have exactly one ArtObjectContext and an Factory that knows how to create the context, a new instance of the art object and how to load the configuration of the art object.

      • meta

        ArtObjectMeta<TArtObject> meta()
        Returns:
        the meta information of the art object created by this factory

      • create

        TArtObject create​(ConfigMap configMap)
        Creates a new ArtObject instance provided by this factory with the given configuration.

        The created object will have its field injected that are defined in the provided ConfigMap.

        The object will be created automtically by the ArtObjectContext that is created with the createContext(ContextConfig) method.

        Parameters:
        configMap - the config map that holds the config information of the object
        Returns:
        a new art object instance for the type of this factory

      • createContext

        TContext createContext​(ContextConfig config)
        Creates a new ArtObjectContext that controls the execution flow of the ArtObject.

        The context will dynamically create new instances of the ArtObject using create(ConfigMap).

        Parameters:
        config - the configuration maps of the context
        Returns:
        a new instance of the art object context defined as the context type of this factory
